                  "adjusted_stars": 4.92525,
                  "stars": 5.0,
                  "text": "OMG...  Best Mexican Food in the Valley!!  \n\nLet's do the bad stuff first.  Saturday afternoon around 5pm.  There was ZERO parking.  The neighborhood is sketchy at best.  Seating is extremely limited.  \n\nNow the good.  Close access to the freeway.  Friendly cashier!  Quick ordering to go.  Busboys turn over tables quickly too.  Inexpensive delicious food.  \n\n$1.50 for Tacos Al Vapor (Beef, Beans, Chicken or Chicharron).  \n\nIf this restaurant was closer I wouldn't have to cook.  Wish there was more seating.  Would have loved to have sat and are with the family.  Drive home 35min later and the food was still hot!"
