                  "text": "One of the most romantic places to dine on the canal in the Venetian shops while watching and listening to the gondola rides go by. Excellent Mexican food that will satisfy all types of pallets with a variety of traditional and unique flavorful dishes.\n\nHighly recommend the Tuna Ceviche Tostado with cilantro topping for an appetizer. Its so fresh and spicy. Also a must get is the Santa Rosa Pork Barbacoa which just falls off your fork and melts in your mouth with barbecue sauce.  Another favorite was the wild mushroom enchilada. I also got the Coco Pina drink served in a cute coconut shell which was amazing too.\n\nThe service was excellent and the ambiance was great. Will be back for sure."
