                  "adjusted_stars": 4.9864999999999995,
                  "stars": 5.0,
                  "text": "DOING IT RIGHT \n\nLet me start with saying I'm from Kansas City and being the beer drinking food loving guy I am I have had my share of good and bad BBQ. So let's get started, first off the location is perfect it's right in the middle of everything you'll be doing on Fremont. \n\nThe atmosphere is perfect you have the flashy food truck parked inside with plenty of tables to stand at to enjoy your meal. While eating you can look around and see the signatures of all the previous guests from around the globe who have signed the walls, be sure to locate the manager and ask for the sharpie so you can join the club.\n\n Let's get down to the food, we had the brisket sandwich and let me tell you it's not the Kansas City style I was expecting, but let me say my mind was BLOWN!!  I was served a large, soft yet firm hoagie stuffed with tender brisket topped with delicious slaw finished with a mouth watering sweet yet spicy sauce that was drizzled over the meat and made its way to the bread but never made the sandwich soggy, probably because I shoved it in my face as fast as humanly possible because it tasted so good.\n\nYou can tell this wasn't made by some sloppy hillbilly standing in his back yard burning meat on a junkie old smoker. This was put together by the hands of a experienced chief who knows their way around a kitchen. I can tell you that most BBQ is really just plain meat that needs sauce to force it down. This in not that food. Everything on the sandwich flows together for perfect food harmony creating the ultimate orgasmic tastebud experience, sorry for the detail but i figured I should warn you in case you need to bring an extra pair of pants. You will not leave hungry and for me that's always a plus. If you want good food for a good price this is your spot!! And if your traveling from one of the BBQ Mecca's like Kansas City, Texas, Memphis or the Carolinas I would absolutely put this place on the map as a must visit."
