                  "text": "So I am very picky with Mexican food. Especially if its supposed to be authentic.\n\nThis place is located on Fremont Street right next to Common Wealth. The inside is nice and very old school. Kinda like day of the dead. There is also a swing located by the bar. Which I didn't see anybody ride. LOL \n\nWe started our dinner with a passion fruit margarita, which was actually really yummy and I just had me a regular modelo beer.I ordered the ceviche which came with plantain chips, I thought it was kind of different. I preferred the ceviche with the tortilla chips that they served when you get there. I also thought it would be a big portion of ceviche but obviously with my picture it wasn't. But enough to get me full. My partner ordered the nachos, served with steak, cheese, guacamole, and jalapenos. They also served the nachos not with tortilla chips. Im not sure what kind of chips they were but they were thick. The nachos were OK. Wasn't a really big fan and the portion was OK as well. I know that when I go to a Mexican restaurant they always serve a big portion of their food. We ended our dinner with the tres leches cake which was really yummy and I guess you could say I would order that cake again.\n\nIm not sure if I would come back to this restaurant, but if I do I think I would have to be really drunk. \n\nOhh and their servers, they talk to each other too much. I shouldn't have to yell for them to fill both my cups of water and ask for more tortilla chips.Just sayin."
