                  "text": "Let me just start by saying, in regards to food, we only had chips, guac, and salsa (which were amazing!). A friend and I wound up here merely because we needed to kill time, and it was close to where we were headed. I cannot say enough good things about this place. Yes, it's small, but I absolutely love the decor and vibe of the place. It was an early Tuesday afternoon (of this week) and we sat at the bar. Unfortunately, I saw no name tag, but our receipt said 'Nicole' was who served us; an African American young lady who was an absolute pleasure. Can't wait to bring my fiance here. The chips were warm and fresh, guac was fresh and served with heirloom tomatoes on top, and both salsas (red and green) were amazing. I cannot WAIT to come back and try more than chips and salsa. As a fellow bartender, I was thoroughly impressed by the drink selection, and the fact they actually have 'mixologists' creating and constructing the drinks. Everything is made fresh. Do yourself a favor and check this place out!"
